  "text": "We compare the mean daytime GEOS-Chem surface ozone concentrations (scaled to 4 m height with varying land types) with observations from the Air Quality System (AQS) network (www.epa.gov/aqs) in the US during summer (JJA) 2010. We find 15 that the model is biased high by ~8 ppb on average. This high bias is consistent with previous studies (e.g., [CITATION_1] .",
